==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lovelock
<hw>Love"lock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A long lock of hair
hanging prominently by itself; an earlock; -- worn by men of fashion in
the reigns of Elizabeth and James I.</def> <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A long <qex>lovelock</qex> and long hair he wore.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lovelorn</ent>⟦br⟧
